  "prompt": "What universities does First Midwest Bank recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "First Midwest Bank, now part of Old National Bank following their merger, typically recruits new graduates from a variety of universities and looks for individuals with diverse educational backgrounds. While specific universities can vary, they often target institutions recognized for strong business, finance, and economics programs.\n\nCommon universities can include:\n- University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n- DePaul University\n- Northern Illinois University\n- Loyola University Chicago\n- University of Wisconsin-Madison\n- Indiana University Bloomington\n- Purdue University\n\nRegarding majors, First Midwest Bank is likely looking for graduates in fields such as:\n- Finance\n- Accounting\n- Business Administration\n- Economics\n- Marketing \n- Information Technology\n- Data Analytics\n\nThey may also be interested in candidates with strong skills in mathematics, communication, and problem-solving, reflecting the broad range of roles available within the banking sector. It\u2019s always best to check directly with the bank for the most current recruitment information.",
